All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AuthData
The AuthData class provides utility methods for managing the current authenticated user within the application.
AuthService
The abstract class AuthService used as a base for authentication services in this application.
AuthStaffService
The class AuthStaffService extends from the abstract class AuthService.
AuthStudentService
The class AuthStudentService extends from the abstract class AuthService.
Camp
The Camp class represents a camp in the system.
CampComController
The StudentController class is responsible for handling the camp committee-specific user interface and user interactions.
CampComMem
The CampComMem class represents a committee member of a camp.
CampComMenu
The CampComMenu implements the generic menu, Menu.
CampInfo
The CampInfo class contains all information on a Camp that inherits it.
CampManagementService
TheCampManagementService class provides methods to generate reports that can be called by both StaffController and CampComController
CAMsApp
The main class responsible for running the CAMs application.
ColouredTextPrinter
The class ColouredTextPrinter prints color text in the console using ANSI escape codes.
Database
The Database class manages the data storage within the application.
DatabaseService
The DatabaseService class provides methods to reading and writing of data into CSV file for student,staff and camp entities
Enquiries
The Enquiries class represents an inquiry submitted to a camp by a student.
EnquiriesService
The EnquiriesService class is responsible in managing the enquiries of a specified camp This class provides methods in creating and viewing of enquiries
Faculty
The Faculty enum represents various faculties in NTU in the system.
HelperService
The HelperService class provides utility methods in various tasks related to the application
LoginMenu
The LoginMenu implements the generic menu, Menu.
MainMenu
The MainMenu implements the generic menu, Menu.
Menu
The Menu interface represents the generic menu that defines printMenu() and viewApp() functions
OutOfRange
Additonal class to handle out of range exceptions
Staff
The Staff class represents a staff user in the system.
StaffCampMenu
The StaffCampMenu implements the generic menu, Menu.
StaffCampService
The class StaffCampService is responsible in managing the camp-related functionalities for staff users.
StaffController
The StaffController class is responsible for handling the staff-specific user interface and user interactions.
StaffMenu
The StaffMenu implements the generic menu, Menu.
Student
The Student class represents a student user in the system.
StudentCampMenu
The StudentCampMenu implements the generic menu, Menu.
StudentCampService
The class StudentCampService is responsible in managing the camp-related functionalities for student users
StudentController
The StudentController class is responsible for handling the student-specific user interface and user interactions.
StudentMenu
The StudentMenu implements the generic menu, Menu.
Suggestions
The Suggestions class represents a suggestion submitted to a camp by a camp committee member.
SuggestionsService
The class SuggestionsService provides methods in managing the Suggestions of a specific camp
SuggestionStatus
The SuggestionsStatus enum represents the suggestions status in the system.
User
The User class represents a user in the system.
UserController
The UserController class is responsible for handling user-related actions, such as changing the user's password.
UserService
The class UserService provides method to change user's password
